<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,612]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
Comment: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[326,499,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecila">
<emphasis box="[326,499,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Centris poecila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was correctly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Snelling, R. R." box="[834,1011,513,539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="1 - 41" refId="ref11444" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1974) Notes on the distribution and taxonomy of some North American Centris (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 259, 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1974">Snelling (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[1068,1296,513,539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref10644" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1152,1202,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
. Despite the existence of published distribution records in Central America, as well as in other Caribbean islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Genaro, J. A." box="[1267,1424,549,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="247 - 254" refId="ref9950" refString="Genaro, J. A. (2007) Las abejas (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila) de La Hispaniola, Antillas. Boletin Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 40, 247 - 254." type="journal article" year="2007">Genaro, 2007</bibRefCitation>
), apparently it only occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[465,524,585,611]" name="Cuba" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
